# CONVENTIONAL COMMITS

## FORMAT
```
<type>[scope]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

## TYPES
`feat` | `fix` | `docs` | `style` | `refactor` | `perf` | `test` | `build` | `ci` | `chore` | `revert`

## SCOPES (Jmix/Vaadin)
`jmix` | `vaadin` | `entity` | `view` | `service` | `security` | `liquibase` | `ui` | `api` | `db` | `config` | `test`

## RULES
- Imperative mood: "add" not "added"/"adds"
- Lowercase, no period, max 72 chars (50 preferred)
- Body: WHAT/WHY, wrap 72, bullets for multiple
- Footer: `BREAKING CHANGE:`, `Closes #123`, `Fixes #456`
- Breaking: `type!:` or footer `BREAKING CHANGE:`

## EXAMPLES
```
feat(vaadin): add login form component
fix(jmix): resolve DataManager null pointer
refactor(service): extract payment calculation logic
refactor(service): separate REDUCE_TERM and REDUCE_PAYMENT handling

Refactor early payment handling to support separate processing.
Adjust remaining balance and loan term accordingly.

feat(service)!: migrate to virtual threads

BREAKING CHANGE: Service methods now return CompletableFuture
```

